’Щ@858a4f0ad30e227406a2a749da71c66474470360ccd6f75587018883c5c91069Ъ_Title: title: sleep
Path: Examples
Content:
Sleep for 1 second.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> sleep 1sec


```
Use multiple arguments to write a duration with multiple units, which is unsupported by duration literals.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> sleep 1min 30sec


```
Send output after 1 second.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> sleep 1sec; echo done


```
